.TH "__pcie_print_link_status" 9 "__pcie_print_link_status" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__pcie_print_link_status \- Report the PCI device's link speed and width
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __pcie_print_link_status
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "bool verbose "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
PCI device to query
.IP "verbose" 12
Print info even when enough bandwidth is available
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the available bandwidth at the device is less than the device is
capable of, report the device's maximum possible bandwidth and the
upstream link that limits its performance.  If \fIverbose\fP, always print
the available bandwidth, even if the device isn't constrained.
